HN3[]  Clean Water Act, Water Quality Standards
Under the Federal Water Pollution Control Act, 33 U.S.C.S. § 1251 et seq., the Environmental Protection Agency may not issue an National Pollutant Discharge Elimination System permit without state certification that the permit conforms to state water quality standards. A state has the authority to deny certification of the permit application or attach conditions to the final permit. 33 U.S.C.S. § 1341.

