  LAW §30  > Federal Water Pollution Control Act -- noncompliance with permit requirements -- scope of judicial relief --  > Headnote: LEdHN[1A][] [1A]LEdHN[1B][] [1B]LEdHN[1C][] [1C]
The Federal Water Pollution Control Act (33 USCS 1251 et seq.) does not require a Federal District Court to enjoin immediately all discharges that do not comply with the Act's permit requirements, but rather permits a District Court to order that relief it considers necessary to secure prompt compliance with the Act, such relief including, but not being limited to, an order of immediate cessation. (Stevens, J., dissented from this holding.)
 
